        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 4:38PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 438 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Alston, or 9 miles
southeast of Mount Vernon. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Uvalda, Alston, Rock Springs, South Thompson, and Center.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
